    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Lieutenant General Alvan C. Gillem,
                            Jr., to Brigadier General Henry A.
                            Byroade, at Peiping</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d344</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">344</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-03-30T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="344" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Lieutenant General <persName type="from">Alvan C. Gillem,
                            Jr.</persName>, to Brigadier General <persName type="to">Henry A.
                            Byroade</persName>, at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-30">30 March
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>403. At Committee of Three meeting General Chang<note n="46" xml:id="d344fn46">Gen. Chang Chih-chung, Chinese Government member of the Committee of
                        Three.</note> assured me that instructions regarding the field teams would
                    be passed to Northeast Headquarters. 1289 refers. Again yesterday morning
                    Colonel Pee<note n="47" xml:id="d344fn47">Col. Peter T. K. Pee, aide to
                        Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek.</note> assured me that instructions had been
                    issued. Last night I saw the Gimo who said he would personally take up the
                    matter.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
